& [SourceSet] is the checked research surface
  + [source_001] is Evan Miller, A regularity criterion for the Navier-Stokes equation involving only the middle eigenvalue of the strain tensor
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/1710.05569
    = source_status: arXiv and Arch. Rational Mech. Anal. journal reference
    = relevance: derives a strain equation, enstrophy-growth identity, and scale-critical criteria depending on the positive part of the middle strain eigenvalue
  + [source_002] is Evan Miller, Finite-time blowup for a Navier-Stokes model equation for the self-amplification of strain
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.05415
    = source_status: arXiv and Analysis & PDE journal reference
    = relevance: shows that the enstrophy-growth identity and strain constraint space alone are not sufficient for global regularity in a model equation
  + [source_003] is Evan Miller, On the interaction of strain and vorticity for solutions of the Navier-Stokes equation
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.02691
    = source_status: arXiv and Pure Appl. Analysis journal reference
    = relevance: gives a new divergence-free identity involving strain and vorticity, plus regularity criteria clarifying when advection depletes nonlinearity

& [ResearchResolution] is the strain-eigenframe result
  + [confirmed_001_exact_dynamics_exist] is the strain route is not merely metaphorical; literature derives strain equations and identities tied to enstrophy growth
  + [confirmed_002_middle_eigenvalue_is_structural] is positive middle eigenvalue control gives scale-critical regularity criteria and restricts possible blowup geometry
  + [confirmed_003_model_obstruction_is_serious] is a strain self-amplification model can blow up despite sharing enstrophy-growth identity and constraint structure with the full strain equation
  + [confirmed_004_newer_identity_is_promising_periphery] is the 2024/2026 strain-vorticity identity suggests a way to separate nonlinearity depletion by advection from growth mechanisms

